{"about_the_game":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong><i><u>&quot;Stories to Tell&quot;</u></i></strong> is a series of psychological horror games developed by a 15-year-old boy in which each installment is based on a dream or nightmare that I, the developer, have had. This is a game you won't want to miss...</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Hello, my name is zebaxx, I am a 15-year-old Spanish game developer. I had this nightmare in the summer of 2023. I remember it clearly because I always write down my nightmares when I wake up.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">In <u><i><strong>[Stories to Tell] Greyville Stay</strong></i></u> I had just gotten home one normal afternoon after a long day, when I suddenly realized that some pretty strange things were happening at home...</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">[The game is approximately 15-20 minute]</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">[The aspect ratio can be changed in the SETTINGS menu] </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3240540/extras/Stories_to_tell_1_gif_steam_page.gif?t=1736324513\" /></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong><i><u>Gameplay</u></i></strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Stories to Tell is a walking simulator, with dialogues between the character and npc`s. The game is in first person and it includes things such as being able to play games in your in-game pc and more...</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">key features of <u><i><strong>[Stories to Tell] Greyville Stay</strong></i></u></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">-VHS aesthetics.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">-Dialogues between characters.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">-VHS Aspect Ratio.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>*Whishlist now to support me :)* </strong></p>","background":"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3240540/page_bg_generated_v6b.jpg?t=1736324513","backgroun